The paper is about developing machine learning-based strategies for theorem proving in Higher-Order Logic (HOL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses various machine learning tasks and benchmarks different models, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for generating and filtering logical steps, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of using machine learning in theorem proving, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
